# CROSS-REQ-04 - Governance & Execution Boundary Review Report

Date: 2026-06-10

Workspace: `/opt/Axodus`

## Summary

CROSS-REQ-04 created the Axodus governance and execution boundary review, execution authority matrix, blocked action registry and boundary conflict register.

The review confirms that no nucleus currently has production-sensitive execution authority. Business remains non-executive. Execution-sensitive domains remain owned by their nuclei and blocked behind explicit review gates.

Assessment: GOVERNANCE_EXECUTION_BOUNDARY_REVIEW_ESTABLISHED.

## Workspace State

Root workspace inspected: `/opt/Axodus`

Business repository path resolved to `/mnt/d/Rede/Github/Axodus/Business`.

## Root Versioning State

`/opt/Axodus` is not a Git repository. Global files created and updated under `/opt/Axodus/.instructions` are local/unversioned.

## Input Artifacts Reviewed

- CROSS-REQ-01 Global Opportunity Registry and report.
- CROSS-REQ-02 Cross-Nucleus Dependency Registry, graph summary and report.
- CROSS-REQ-03 Readiness/Ownership Alignment, ownership matrix, readiness gap register and report.
- Business risk/governance classification, dependency/integration map, product catalog and portfolio handoff.
- Global portfolio status, roadmap, maturity register and blocker register.
- Nucleus-level STATUS, SECURITY, BLOCKER_REGISTER, HANDOFF, VALIDATION and maturity assessment files where present.

## Nuclei Scanned

14 nuclei were scanned:

Core, Governance, Documentation, Dex, Defi, AxodusAPP, Business, Marketplace, Academy, Mining, ACS, Trading, BBA-Agency and Lottery.

## Governance Authority Summary

Governance packages can be prepared by multiple nuclei when relevant, but proposal submission, approval, rejection, execution and DAO registry mutation remain blocked unless Governance separately approves an execution path. Governance is the authority nucleus for governance execution, but current execution is not authorized.

## Treasury Authority Summary

Treasury-sensitive modeling/readiness can be prepared by relevant nuclei and Business, but treasury movement, custody, settlement, revenue distribution, payouts and billing execution remain blocked. Defi/Treasury is the current mapped review path, but formal treasury ownership still needs resolution.

## Execution Authority Summary

No `EXECUTION_AUTHORIZED` classification was assigned.

Execution-sensitive actions remain blocked for:

- Governance execution;
- Treasury movement;
- Wallet signing;
- On-chain writes;
- Trading execution;
- DEX swaps/routing/liquidity;
- Marketplace settlement/payment/minting;
- Mining provider execution/payouts;
- Lottery randomness/prize/payout;
- ACS/MCP provisioning/autonomy;
- Production credentials/databases/users/billing.

## Production Authority Summary

No nucleus can currently claim production readiness, operate production services, use production credentials/databases, serve external users or handle user funds under this review.

